{
  "texts": [
    "• Autonomous Workflow Orchestration & Interaction Topology Optimization: By continuously negotiating and replanning, agents autonomously decompose tasks [23],assign subtasks [41], and adjust execution flows [40].",
    "Besides, they autonomously optimize interaction topologies [44], e.g., deciding agent turn-taking in negotiations, to enhance efficiency in dynamic environments.",
    "• Adaptive Conflict Resolution and Consensus: Through contextual negotiation, agents can autonomously detect and resolve conflicts, reconcile competing goals, and reach agreement on consensus strategies [7], [45].2) High Dynamics.",
    "IoA networks are inherently dynamic, characterized by the on-demand creation, migration, and termination of virtual agents, as well as the physical mobility of embodied agents such as UAVs and robots.",
    "This agility enables real-time reconfiguration of agent teams to accommodate varying task demands, environmental conditions, or resource constraints."
  ]
}